; Module-definition file for the injected virtual file system DLL.
;
; Microsoft Detours injects a payload DLL by rewriting the target executable's
; import table to import *ordinal #1* from it (see Detours' uimports.cpp:
; "pt[0] = IMAGE_ORDINAL_FLAG + 1"). The Windows loader therefore refuses to
; start any process we inject into unless this DLL actually exports something at
; ordinal 1 -- without it the game (and every child process we propagate into)
; dies on startup with STATUS_ORDINAL_NOT_FOUND and the VFS never runs.
;
; Following the Detours samples, we re-export Detours' own
; DetourFinishHelperProcess at ordinal 1 (NONAME). It is pulled in from the
; statically linked Detours library and is also the entry point Detours invokes
; in the helper process used for cross-bitness injection.
EXPORTS
    DetourFinishHelperProcess @1 NONAME
